Package aima.core.logic.fol.kb.data

Class Summary
Chain A Chain is a sequence of literals (while a clause is a set) - order is important for a chain.
Clause A Clause: A disjunction of literals.
CNF Conjunctive Normal Form (CNF) : a conjunction of clauses, where each clause is a disjunction of literals.
Literal Artificial Intelligence A Modern Approach (3rd Edition): page 244.

A literal is either an atomic sentence (a positive literal) or a negated atomic sentence (a negative literal).
